Yeah, piece of cake. Shoot.

16:04.380 --> 16:07.633
If you and Mom hated each other so much,
why did you get married?

16:08.175 --> 16:10.177
We didn't start out
hating each other.

16:10.928 --> 16:13.931
Things got dark after I lost my job.

16:15.182 --> 16:17.184
That's your excuse?

16:17.267 --> 16:20.187
It had nothing to do with
the excessive drinking or the affairs?

16:21.021 --> 16:24.024
I'm an alcoholic,
and I was a shitty father.

16:24.608 --> 16:26.902
And while I'm laying it
all out there,

16:26.986 --> 16:28.737
your mother and I were
never really in love,

16:28.821 --> 16:30.531
-so when things got a little rough...
-That's nice.

16:30.614 --> 16:32.116
...we took it out on each other.

16:33.701 --> 16:35.285
I only stayed for you.

16:39.623 --> 16:41.291
Well, I guess you got over me.

16:41.375 --> 16:43.544
Was it the braces

16:43.627 --> 16:45.212
Something I said?

16:47.339 --> 16:51.427
When I left, I-I told myself
that it was the best thing for you.

16:52.428 --> 16:56.223
But now, I realize that I was just doing
what drunks do when things get hard.

16:56.849 --> 16:58.434
I ran away.

17:00.185 --> 17:04.231
And I know they're just words,
but I need to say them.

17:06.025 --> 17:07.443
I'm sorry.

17:09.278 --> 17:13.449
And you will never
know how much, Izzy.

17:18.454 --> 17:20.164
There's one more stop.

17:27.129 --> 17:29.840
Hey. Hi, hi. Hello.

17:29.923 --> 17:32.092
Um, this, what you're doing...

17:32.176 --> 17:33.677
It's against FDA rules, okay?

17:33.761 --> 17:37.389
Something about saliva
and the fact that it's fucking annoying.

17:37.473 --> 17:39.224
Yeah, so if you guys
don't stop immediately,

17:39.308 --> 17:41.477
I'm gonna have to punch you
both in the face,

17:41.560 --> 17:44.480
and I don't wanna.
Sorry. It's the law, so...

17:45.064 --> 17:46.607
Sorry. Shaun, what do you want?

17:46.690 --> 17:49.193
I'm not in the mood to be
berated about how little I work.

17:49.276 --> 17:50.986
Okay, for the record,
you basically get paid

17:51.070 --> 17:53.363
to hang around at a bar
that you already hung around at.

17:53.906 --> 17:56.909
Which, saying it out loud, makes me
think that it's a pretty cool idea.

17:57.326 --> 17:59.745
Hey, and you and your bestie
have violence issues!

17:59.828 --> 18:01.705
Deal with it. Get a Groupon.

18:07.169 --> 18:08.253
What's wrong?

18:11.590 --> 18:14.843
Fucker keeps posting these weird pictures
of him and his dad

18:14.927 --> 18:17.221
somewhere in the woods,
smiling all over themselves.

18:17.304 --> 18:19.640
Why the hell are they
in the woods all the time?!

18:19.723 --> 18:23.310
Right, I-I'm thinking it's not so much
the woods as it is the...

18:23.936 --> 18:28.190
...excessive smiling. Am I right?
I mean, how dare he be so happy?

18:28.273 --> 18:31.777
Ow! You gotta stop doing that!
You got these bony, little knuckles.

18:32.319 --> 18:34.113
-Pussy.
-Psycho.

18:36.490 --> 18:37.533
Okay.

18:39.785 --> 18:41.954
My best, most logical guess is that...

18:42.579 --> 18:46.250
clearly a zombie outbreak has happened
somewhere near Salem, Oregon,

18:46.333 --> 18:48.585
and they've taken
to the woods to survive.

18:48.669 --> 18:53.132
And it's all shits and giggles
for, you know, dad and son here,

18:53.215 --> 18:55.759
and they're just shitting and...
and giggling

18:55.843 --> 18:59.972
and building lean-tos until
someone's face gets eaten off, which...

19:00.973 --> 19:04.977
clearly hasn't happened yet,
and that's why they're there, so...

19:05.435 --> 19:08.730
Mystery solved. Occam's razor.
You're welcome. Next.

19:08.814 --> 19:11.775
You are so fuckin' weird.

19:19.533 --> 19:21.368
-It's cute.
-Mm.

19:24.997 --> 19:27.499
If you'd asked me a year ago
where would we be right now,

19:27.583 --> 19:29.751
I would've said:
on your favourite rug

19:29.835 --> 19:32.045
in our perfect
Hawthorne Heights home,

19:32.796 --> 19:34.381
staring at our baby,

19:34.464 --> 19:38.802
interpreting every burp or shit
as a sure sign of future greatness.

19:38.886 --> 19:40.304
Yeah. We would've been that couple

19:41.889 --> 19:44.016
posting a hundred
indistinguishable baby photos

19:44.099 --> 19:47.311
on Instagram when really one
would be just boring enough.

19:50.856 --> 19:52.941
When did you stop wanting kids?

19:55.027 --> 19:56.111
There wasn't one moment.

19:56.195 --> 19:59.573
It just kinda happened
gradually over the years.

19:59.656 --> 20:02.659
Ever consider talking
to me about it?

20:04.745 --> 20:05.746
I did.

20:05.829 --> 20:08.081
You just never heard me.

20:10.876 --> 20:12.836
So that's how you sleep at night.

20:13.170 --> 20:15.255
-I've wondered.
-And how do you sleep at night

20:15.339 --> 20:18.383
ever since Izzy's high-functioning uterus
became the centre of your world?

20:18.467 --> 20:21.678
Please tell me I did not
just fucking hear that.

20:21.762 --> 20:25.015
Hold on a sec.
I don't get a side to this story?

20:25.098 --> 20:27.142
No. You absolutely,
100% do not.

20:27.226 --> 20:29.311
Jack, admit it:
it was just a matter of time

20:29.394 --> 20:33.190
